    • Field Detail

      • FULL_DOCUMENT_IMAGE

        public static final java.lang.String FULL_DOCUMENT_IMAGE
        Name of the image sent to MetadataListener that contains full document. This image will be sent to MetadataListener during recognition process if displaying of full document image is enabled (see setShowFullDocument(boolean), and receiving of ImageType.DEWARPED image is enabled with MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean)

      • MRZ_IMAGE

        public static final java.lang.String MRZ_IMAGE
        Name of the image sent to MetadataListener that contains machine readable zone. This image will be sent to MetadataListener during recognition process if displaying image of machine readable zone is enabled (see setShowMRZ(boolean), and receiving of ImageType.DEWARPED image is enabled with MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean)

      • setAllowUnparsedResults

        public void setAllowUnparsedResults(boolean allowUnparsed)
        Set this to true to allow obtaining results that have not been parsed by SDK. By default this is off. The reason for this is that we want to ensure best possible data quality when returning results. For that matter we internally parse the MRZ and extract all data, taking all possible OCR mistakes into account. However, if you happen to have a document with MRZ that has format our internal parser still does not support, you need to allow returning of unparsed results. Unparsed results will not contain parsed data, but will contain OCR result received from OCR engine, so you can parse data yourself.
        Parameters:
        allowUnparsed - allow returning of unparsed OCR data

      • setAllowUnverifiedResults

        public void setAllowUnverifiedResults(boolean allowUnverifiedResults)
        Set this to true to allow obtaining of results with incorrect check digits. This flag will be taken into account only if Machine Readable Zone has been successfully parsed because only in that case check digits can be examined.
        Parameters:
        allowUnverifiedResults - allow returning of unverified results

        public void setShowMRZ(boolean showMRZ)
        Set this to true if you use MetadataListener and you want to obtain image containing only Machine Readable Zone. The reported ImageType will be ImageType.DEWARPED and image name will be MRZ_IMAGE. By default, this is turned off.
        Parameters:

      • setShowFullDocument

        public void setShowFullDocument(boolean showFullDocument)
        Set this to true if you use MetadataListener and you want to obtain image containing full document containing Machine Readable Zone. The document image's orientation will be corrected. The reported ImageType will be ImageType.DEWARPED and image name will be FULL_DOCUMENT_IMAGE. By default, this is turned off. When enabling this, make sure you enabled receiving of dewarped image metadata in MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean).
        Parameters:
        showFullDocument - true to obtain image containing full document containing MRZ

      • setParserDecodingInfos

        public void setParserDecodingInfos(@Nullable
                                   DecodingInfo[] decodingInfos)
        Sets the decoding infos for desired additional document elements that should be recognized together with MRZ zone. Use this method if document contains additional information (elements) of interest that should be recognized together with MRZ and only one document type is expected. The position of each additional element is represented as DecodingInfo object which holds the location for that element of interest (relative to full document detection) and the desired dewarp height (in number of pixels), for that location. Name of the decoding info must be equal to the name of the parser group that will be used for parsing that element.
        If you want to support the multiple document types containing MRZ, and if they can be distinguished using the MRZ result and fields defined in locations set in this method, use method setParserDecodingInfos(DecodingInfo[], String) for setting the decoding infos for each document type and method setDocumentClassifier(MRTDDocumentClassifier) for setting the document classifier.
        Parameters:
        decodingInfos - Array that contains the decoding infos for additional document elements of interest that should be recognized together with MRZ. If null is set, then only the recognition of MRZ will be performed, as by default.

      • setParserDecodingInfos

        public void setParserDecodingInfos(@NonNull
                                   DecodingInfo[] decodingInfos,
                                   @NonNull
                                   java.lang.String decodingInfoSet)
        Sets the named decoding info set, for specific document type, whose elements contain location information about additional document elements that should be recognized together with the MRZ zone. Use this method if document contains additional information (elements) of interest that should be recognized together with MRZ zone and there are multiple document types that can be distinguished using the MRZ result.
        The position of each additional element is represented as DecodingInfo object which holds the location for that element of interest (relative to full document detection) and the desired dewarp height (in number of pixels), for that location. Name of the decoding info must be equal to the name of the parser group that will be used for parsing that element.
        Additionally, for document classification, set the document classifier using the method setDocumentClassifier(MRTDDocumentClassifier).
        Overrides:
        setParserDecodingInfos in class TemplatingRecognizerSettings
        Parameters:
        decodingInfos - Array that contains the decoding infos for additional document elements of interest that should be recognized together with the MRZ zone.
        decodingInfoSet - Name of the decoding info set, must be equal to the classifier result for corresponding document type.

      • setDocumentClassifier

        public void setDocumentClassifier(@Nullable
                                  MRTDDocumentClassifier documentClassifier)
        Sets the MRTDDocumentClassifier that can be used for classification of the documents based on the MRZ zone result. This method should be used if multiple MRTD document types are expected and additional information (elements) of interest should be recognized. In addition, decoding infos for each document type should be set with method setParserDecodingInfos(DecodingInfo[], String) method. For each document type, name of the decoding info set must be equal to corresponding classifier result.
        Parameters:
        documentClassifier - Document classifier that will be used for document classification based on the MRZ results. Classifier result, for each document type, must be equal to the name of the corresponding decoding info set for that document type.

      • setMRZFilter

        public void setMRZFilter(@Nullable
                         MRZFilter mrzFilter)
        Sets the MRZFilter that will be used for filtering MRTD documents based on the MRZ zone result. MRZ filter should be used if only specific MRTD documents should be processed. Only recognition results from documents that are allowed by this filter can be returned.
        Parameters:
        mrzFilter - MRZ filter that will be used for document filtering based on the MRZ results.
